<c74object name='sp.datagranular' category='' module='SP-Tools'>
    <digest>Repeat and vary incoming descriptor data like a &#39;granular synth&#39;
</digest>
    <description>Repeat and vary incoming descriptor data like a &#39;granular synth&#39;.
</description>
    <discussion><h4><openfilelink filename="SP-Tools Overview.maxpat">Open the Overview Patch</openfilelink></h4>
The <o>sp.datagranular</o> object takes incoming descriptor data (descriptors, melbands, MFCCs, or sines) and processes it through a &#39;granular synth&#39;-style process. The input can be lists or <o>buffer~</o> s and the same will be output.
</discussion>

	<metadatalist>
		<metadata name='author'>Rodrigo Constanzo, Flucoma Project</metadata>
		<metadata name='tag'>Machine Learning</metadata>
		<metadata name='tag'>Audio Analysis</metadata>
		<metadata name='tag'>Onset Detection</metadata>
		<metadata name='tag'>Corpus Playback</metadata>
	</metadatalist>

    <!-- INLETS -->
    <inletlist>
        <inlet id='0' type='list'>
            <digest>Descriptor and control in
</digest>
            <description>Incoming descriptors as a list or <o>buffer~</o> as well as control input.
</description>
        </inlet>
    </inletlist>
    <!-- INLETS -->

    <!-- OUTLETS -->
    <outletlist>
        <outlet id='0' type='list'>
            <digest>Descriptor output
</digest>
            <description>Transformed descriptor output.
</description>
        </outlet>
    </outletlist>
    <!-- OUTLETS -->

    <!-- ARGUMENTS -->
    <objarglist>
    </objarglist>
    <!-- ARGUMENTS -->

    <!--MESSAGES-->
    <methodlist>
    <method name='enable'>
        <arglist>
        </arglist>
        <digest>Enable the granular process
</digest>
        <description>Enables/disables the granular process.
</description>
    </method>
	</methodlist>
	<!--MESSAGES-->

